39// Specializes a given JSGraph to a given native context, potentially constant
40// folding some {LoadGlobal} nodes or strength reducing some {StoreGlobal}
41// nodes. And also specializes {LoadNamed} and {SetNamedProperty} nodes
42// according to type feedback (if available).
43class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE JSNativeContextSpecialization final
44 : public AdvancedReducer {
45 public:
46 // Flags that control the mode of operation.
47 enum Flag {
48 kNoFlags = 0u,
49 kBailoutOnUninitialized = 1u << 0,
50 };
51 using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>;
52
53 JSNativeContextSpecialization(Editor* editor, JSGraph* jsgraph,
54 JSHeapBroker* broker, Flags flags, Zone* zone,
55 Zone* shared_zone);
56 JSNativeContextSpecialization(const JSNativeContextSpecialization&) = delete;
57 JSNativeContextSpecialization& operator=(
58 const JSNativeContextSpecialization&) = delete;
59
60 const char* reducer_name() const override {
61 return "JSNativeContextSpecialization";
62 }
63
64 Reduction Reduce(Node* node) final;

69 static base::Optional<size_t> GetMaxStringLength(JSHeapBroker* broker,
70 Node* node);

72 private:
73 Reduction ReduceJSAdd(Node* node);

131 // A triple of nodes that represents a continuation.
132 class ValueEffectControl final {
133 public:
134 ValueEffectControl()
135 : value_(nullptr), effect_(nullptr), control_(nullptr) {}
136 ValueEffectControl(Node* value, Node* effect, Node* control)
137 : value_(value), effect_(effect), control_(control) {}
138
139 Node* value() const { return value_; }
140 Node* effect() const { return effect_; }
141 Node* control() const { return control_; }
142
143 private:
144 Node* value_;
145 Node* effect_;
146 Node* control_;
147 };

217 // Returns true if {str} can safely be read:
218 // - if we are on the main thread, then any string can safely be read
219 // - in the background, we can only read some string shapes, except if we
220 // created the string ourselves.
221 // {node} is the node from which we got {str}, but which is still taken as
222 // parameter to simplify the checks.
223 bool StringCanSafelyBeRead(Node* const node, Handle<String> str);
224
